HEADWORD: lobster-backed
<hw>lobster-backed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(American History)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to British soldiers during the Revolutionary War
in America; -- so called because of their red coats.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> red-coated.</syn>⟦br⟧
